parameters.name: DATE
parameters.description:
Spacecraft Event Time (SCET) at the start of the first sweep in year,   
                        month and day format (YYMMDD).

parameters.name: SECOND
parameters.description:
Seconds of the day to the nearest second, at the start of the first     
                        sweep.  In each sweep, the first data value in low band (1326.0 kHz)    
                        occurs some 3.9 seconds after this time. Subsequent data points are     
                        sampled at a lower frequency interval of 0.03 second.  Only one time    
                        is given for the entire major frame, thus the start time of each sweep  
                        in the major frame is given by this time plus 6 times the sweep number  
                        minus 1 (i.e. 0 through 7).
